messages.subject: different humor levels
messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 5/13/02 10:26:54 AM, skreams@attbi.com writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 5/13/02 10:26:54 AM, skreams@... writes:

<< There are always a few levels of humor going
on, which I like now and remember liking as a kid when I watched Rocky and
Bullwinkle. >>

Marty and I were discussing this just the other day, about Bugs Bunny
cartoons. There's one level of physical humor for little kids, and the other
script-stuff (and some quiet sight-gags) are for adults.

We also discussed Rocky and Bullwinkle (and related cartoons--George of the
Jungle, Super Chicken, that set). He's really liking seeing things again
now that he's older.

Sandra
